      "file_path": "cps-ri/src/test/java/org/onap/cps/TestApplication.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 29,
      "message": "TestApplication class is in package org.onap.cps, so it tries to load all the component define in it. cps-service is one of the dependencies of cps-ri and also have components defined in org.onap.cps package. So, when TestApplication tried to create application context it loads all the components in cps-service. \nIt was causing test failures in cps-ri when I created a new component in cps-service that uses a configuration from application.yml. \n\n@ComponentScan is also defined @SpringBootApplication so removal should not cause any issue. But, if it was scanning only org.onao.cps.spi package then it may be the cause.",
